T1  - Helpless.
T3  - Family Systems Medicine
A1  - Matalon, Andre

Y1  - 2004//
N2  - This article presents an account of a doctor-patient and family relationship of 20 years duration. Through the narrative, the family physician discloses his feelings and personal insights during the years of accompaniment and treatment of a somatization patient and his family. It describes the very first feelings of kinship through later dreadful feelings of anger, frustration, and helplessness. Understanding the source of helplessness in his own childhood allowed the family physician to develop feelings of personal and professional efficacy and growth. Only by allowing himself to go through this process was he able to be with the patient, to accept his condition, and to treat him and his family more compassionately. This case report illustrates and emphasizes the relational aspects of family medicine. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2025 APA, all rights reserved)
